# Getting started

This guide gets `{{ project_name }}` running on your machine in a couple of minutes.

## Prerequisites

- Python **3.11+**
- `git`

## Install

```bash
git clone <repository-url> {{ project_name }}
cd {{ project_name }}

python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate        # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate

# Core + dev toolchain:
pip install -e ".[dev]"
{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %}
# This is a rest-api service — also install the HTTP extra:
pip install -e ".[api]"
{% endif %}
```

## Run the tests

```bash
pytest
```

You should see the **smoke tests** and the **Hypothesis property tests** pass —
this is the green-from-birth guarantee.

{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %}
## Run the service

```bash
uvicorn {{ package_name }}.api:app --reload
```

Then check the health endpoint:

```bash
curl localhost:8000/health
# {"status":"ok","service":"{{ project_name }}","version":"0.1.0"}
```
{% else %}
## Run the worker

This is a `worker` service: it has no HTTP surface. Wire your entrypoint in
`src/{{ package_name }}/` and invoke it from your process manager / scheduler.
{% endif %}

## Quality checks (what CI runs)

```bash
ruff check .
black --check .
mypy
mkdocs build --strict
```

## Build the docs locally

```bash
mkdocs serve      # live-reloading docs at http://127.0.0.1:8000
```
